headline: Gordon Haskett says California Tylenol case dismissal ‘significant’ Kenvue win
summary: Gordon Haskett reports that the judge overseeing the initial California Tylenol lawsuit against Kenvue (KVUE) granted summary judgement in favor of the defendants in what the firm calls a “significant win” for Kenvue, adding that the firm would expect the only remaining California case that is before the same judge to eventually get dismissed on similar grounds. The decision “significantly boosts” Kenvue’s efforts to tie up loose ends following the 2023 dismissal of all the Tylenol ASD-ADHD case

headline: Edgewell Personal Care (EPC) Q2 Earnings and Revenues Lag Estimates
summary: Edgewell Personal (EPC) delivered earnings and revenue surprises of -3.33% and 1.69%, respectively, for the quarter ended March 2025. Do the numbers hold clues to what lies ahead for the stock?
